This paper deals with the topic of differential privacy, which is a subfield of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of noise mechanisms in data analysis, which is a topic in data structures (cs.DS) and databases (cs.DB). The paper also involves information theory (cs.IT) in its analysis of the tradeoff between privacy and utility. Finally, the paper discusses the optimality of certain mechanisms, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG).
